00:13:06,852 --> 00:13:11,090
And a tutoring position so
you could be alone with him?

235
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:12,992
They were horrible parents.

236
00:13:12,992 --> 00:13:15,227
And I told them so.
Why do you think I got fired?

237
00:13:15,227 --> 00:13:19,113
- Mr. Russo, we know why you were fired.
- What'd you do with Corbin?

238
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:27,540
I listened to him,
I encouraged him.

239
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:29,928
You loved him.

240
00:13:34,213 --> 00:13:38,761
Why'd you bring him
in the bathroom? /  What?

241
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:40,886
No...

242
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:43,289
- you can't be thinking...
- You were obsessed with him...

243
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:46,091
You don't understand.
They wouldn't let me near him.

244
00:13:46,091 --> 00:13:48,327
- You stalked him.
- No, I was leaving town.

245
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:50,162
You were his teacher,
you gained his trust.

246
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:53,861
You knew about his birthday.
You found out where his party was.

247
00:13:56,035 --> 00:13:58,070
You molested him. / No!

248
00:13:58,070 --> 00:14:00,439
Your whole world revolves
around this little boy.

249
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:03,776
Now, why is that?
Explain that to me.

250
00:14:03,776 --> 00:14:06,793
Because he's my son.

251
00:14:15,254 --> 00:14:17,156
The tutor tells you
he's your daddy.

252
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:18,724
That's gotta mess
with a kid's head.

253
00:14:18,724 --> 00:14:21,460
Russo says he never told him,
out of just that concern.

254
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:22,628
A considerate psycho.

255
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:24,330
He got a girl pregnant at 17...

256
00:14:24,330 --> 00:14:26,765
put the baby up for adoption,
signed away all his rights.

257
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:28,667
Ten years later,
it's still nagging at him.

258
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:30,669
So Mr. Computer starts
searching the Net.

259
00:14:30,669 --> 00:14:33,873
Where he gets a hit on a famous couple
with an adopted boy...

260
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,507
fixates on it being his.

261
00:14:35,507 --> 00:14:37,376
The guy's not budging off his story.

262
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:39,278
Then lets give him a little push.

263
00:14:39,278 --> 00:14:42,047
Get on the adoption agency,
and put a rush on the DNA.

264
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:45,351
Still, we don't have a living CW,
an eyewitness or forensics.

265
00:14:45,351 --> 00:14:47,987
- No confession, no case...
- No excuses.

266
00:14:47,987 --> 00:14:50,990
I've got media sniffing around
and the brass chomping at my ass.

267
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:53,567
I want this closed yesterday.

268
00:14:55,694 --> 00:14:58,764
SVU, Detective Benson.

269
00:14:58,764 --> 00:15:03,969
Ashley, are you okay?

270
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:06,438
We'll be right there.

271
00:15:07,853 --> 00:15:10,376
NEW YORK
CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL
579 FIRST AVENUE
TUESDAY, JANUARY 16

272
00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:13,846
- Hi, there.
- Olivia.

273
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:19,385
- Hi. What happened?
- I fell.

274
00:15:19,385 --> 00:15:23,422
- Where?
- My stairs at home.

275
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:27,059
- Who was with you?
- Nobody.

276
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:29,570
Feel.

277
00:15:31,330 --> 00:15:35,114
That's a goose egg, all right.

278
00:15:36,468 --> 00:15:38,270
Ashley...

279
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:41,006
you would let me know
if there was anything that I could do...

280
00:15:41,006 --> 00:15:43,676
to stop these accidents, wouldn't you?

281
00:15:43,676 --> 00:15:47,806
You can't help accidents.

282
00:15:48,814 --> 00:15:50,649
No parents?

283
00:15:50,649 --> 00:15:53,185
Jared's probably on a plane
back from Europe.

284
00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:56,522
- And Ricki?
- Recording studio.

285
00:15:56,522 --> 00:15:58,891
She's back working already?

286
00:15:58,891 --> 00:16:01,593
People have different ways
of dealing with grief.

287
00:16:01,593 --> 00:16:07,066
Yeah, well, her kid's in the hospital.
Why the hell isn't she here?

288
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,835
I can't.

289
00:16:09,835 --> 00:16:13,472
Everyone who works for them
signs a confidentiality agreement.

290
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:16,442
I could lose my job and be sued.

291
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:19,678
Fair enough.
Where were you when Ashley fell?

292
00:16:19,678 --> 00:16:24,249
Packing up Corbin's room.
I didn't want to drag Ashley through that.

293
00:16:24,249 --> 00:16:26,752
How long have you worked
for them?  / A year.

294
00:16:26,752 --> 00:16:32,624
And in that time,
how many accidents has Ashley had?

295
00:16:32,624 --> 00:16:35,427
She's had accidents all her life.

296
00:16:35,427 --> 00:16:37,162
You don't know
how many I've prevented...

297
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,933
Sarah.
Shouldn't you be with Ashley?

298
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,902
Yeah.

299
00:16:43,902 --> 00:16:46,739
- What are you doing here?
- Ashley called us.

300
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:49,475
We thought we'd come down
and check in on her.

301
00:16:49,475 --> 00:16:52,111
I'm sorry she bothered you.

302
00:16:52,111 --> 00:16:54,586
I won't let it happen again.

303
00:17:00,452 --> 00:17:02,421
Sarah.

304
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:06,158
- Please, I really can't talk to you.
- What's going on with Ashley?

305
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:10,662
You know, a criminal investigation...
supersedes a confidentiality agreement.

306
00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:12,390
Now, if somebody's hurting
this little girl...

307
00:17:12,390 --> 00:17:14,500
No, you misunderstood
what I said.

308
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,552
- I don't think we did.
- Who are you covering for?

309
00:17:16,552 --> 00:17:20,339
- Please, don't do this to me.
- Is it Ricki? Is it Connie?

310
00:17:20,339 --> 00:17:22,998
Just tell us who it is.

311
00:17:26,812 --> 00:17:28,647
Called three times.

312
00:17:28,647 --> 00:17:30,582
- Who? Maureen?
- Not yours, yours.

313
00:17:30,582 --> 00:17:33,786
What? Who, Ashley?
What happened? Is she okay?

314
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:39,024
No, she saw the new NSYNC video
and was sadly disappointed, as was I.

315
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:40,793
She just called to chat.

316
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:43,595
- It's not funny, Munch.
- Yeah, well try this.

317
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:46,899
The adoption agency
and the DNA results confirm it.

318
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:49,835
David Russo is Corbin's biological father.

319
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:52,538
- Let's close this puppy out.
- We can't.

320
00:17:52,538 --> 00:17:55,174
Why?  / Someone might be
abusing the sister.

321
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:58,911
- Don't do this to me. Who?
- We don't know.

322
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,579
- Who made the complaint?
- No one.

323
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:04,116
But this kid has got
a long history of accidents.

324
00:18:04,116 --> 00:18:06,618
- And?
- She says they're accidents.

325
00:18:06,618 --> 00:18:11,123
We can't just fabricate child abuse cases.
Especially with high profiles.

326
00:18:11,123 --> 00:18:14,837
Captain, the nanny was this close
to giving something up to us.

327
00:18:14,837 --> 00:18:16,795
Just let us have
one more shot at her.

328
00:18:16,795 --> 00:18:19,231
The case is closed.
Leave them alone.

329
00:18:19,231 --> 00:18:22,601
Captain, we need to inform
Ricki about Russo.

330
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:24,896
Do it by phone.

331
00:18:28,507 --> 00:18:32,845
Okay, we're in, we're out.
We're not even supposed to be here, right?

332
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:36,415
- Olivia!
- Hey.

333
00:18:36,415 --> 00:18:38,784
Ashley, you're in the middle of a lesson.

334
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:41,887
This is one of my best friends
and I hardly ever get to see her.

335
00:18:41,887 --> 00:18:43,255
You've got 10 minutes left.

336
00:18:43,255 --> 00:18:45,657
Actually, Ashley, I need to talk
to your mom, anyway.

337
00:18:45,657 --> 00:18:49,394
So I'll come say goodbye
before I leave, okay?

338
00:18:49,394 --> 00:18:51,463
Come on.

339
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:54,700
- Are you her piano teacher?
- No, I'm her new nanny.

340
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,970
- What happened to Sarah?
- I'll take care of this.

341
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:02,207
- What's your fascination with our nannies?
- Just how many you go through.

342
00:19:02,207 --> 00:19:05,744
We thought we'd just drop by
to let you know Russo's been cleared.

343
00:19:05,744 --> 00:19:09,815
What? / In fact,
he's Corbin's birth father.

344
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:12,851
- That can't be.
- DNA tests confirmed it.

345
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:15,220
It was a closed adoption.

346
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:18,123
He must have broken
some law to find him. / No.

347
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:21,693
- Was he planning to extort money?
- No.

348
00:19:21,693 --> 00:19:25,697
He just wanted to make sure
that his son was loved.

349
00:19:25,697 --> 00:19:30,402
Don't be naive. Wait and see
how quickly he sells his story.

350
00:19:30,402 --> 00:19:32,371
Ricki didn't even register relief...

351
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:34,573
when she found out that
Corbin hadn't been molested.

352
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:36,208
We did drop a bombshell on her.

353
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:39,278
- Excuse me,
- they took her away.

354
00:19:39,278 --> 00:19:44,516
Who?  / Immigration.
Immigration took her away.

355
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:46,652
Okay, are you talking about Sarah?

356
00:19:46,652 --> 00:19:48,554
She got deported?
Is that what you're saying?

357
00:19:48,554 --> 00:19:53,158
- I'm worried about the little girl.
- Okay, why?

358
00:19:53,158 --> 00:19:55,360
- Why?
- No, I have to go now.

359
00:19:55,360 --> 00:20:00,699
But, miss, please,
you need to talk to us. / No, I can't.

360
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:06,572
What the hell is going on
in that house?

361
00:20:06,572 --> 00:20:09,341
You had no business going
back to that house.

362
00:20:09,341 --> 00:20:11,677
- We were in the neighborhood.
- I dragged him there.

363
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:14,646
You have no grounds
for an investigation.

364
00:20:14,646 --> 00:20:18,250
- Captain, they're covering something up.
- They're celebrities...

365
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,085
people pick through their garbage...

366
00:20:20,085 --> 00:20:23,889
tape their cell phone conversations...
sell their intimate secrets.

367
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:26,458
Covering up is second nature
to these people.

368
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:30,162
Elliot. / Boss, read the ME's report
on the boy. Just talk to her.

369
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:32,097
That kid was a nervous wreck
about something.

370
00:20:32,097 --> 00:20:34,833
It's hot in the limelight and this boy
never asked to be there.

371
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,370
Doesn't explain away Ashley's injuries,
or the fact that the one person who...

372
00:20:38,370 --> 00:20:41,673
- decides to talk about them gets deported.
- And we need to interview her.

373
00:20:41,673 --> 00:20:43,709
She's in England.
What do you want? Air fare?

374
00:20:43,709 --> 00:20:45,978
- We'll take $4 for the tunnel.
- We already checked.

375
00:20:45,978 --> 00:20:50,277
She's still at the INS detention center
in Elizabeth, New Jersey.

376
00:20:57,589 --> 00:21:01,126
I begged you to leave me alone.

377
00:21:01,126 --> 00:21:03,328
We're sorry.

378
00:21:09,001 --> 00:21:12,537
The agent gave me
15 minutes to pack.

379
00:21:12,537 --> 00:21:15,040
Ashley was still at school...

380
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,742
I didn't get to say goodbye.

381
00:21:16,742 --> 00:21:20,245
Sarah, there's nothing more
that they can do to you...

382
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:23,415
but Ashley is still in that house.

383
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:25,183
Please, tell us who's hurting her.

384
00:21:25,183 --> 00:21:27,753
I only wish it were that simple.

385
00:21:27,753 --> 00:21:30,722
Her own mother doesn't have
time for her.

386
00:21:30,722 --> 00:21:33,692
The longer she's away,
the more hyper Ashley gets.

387
00:21:33,692 --> 00:21:38,196
I called Children's Services once,
anonymously.

388
00:21:38,196 --> 00:21:41,400
They do drugs.
Not just Jared. Ricki, too.

389
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,803
- You saw Ricki doing drugs?
- No.

390
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:46,705
But I've seen her looking stoned.

391
00:21:46,705 --> 00:21:48,807
What about that incident
you reported?

392
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:51,343
Ricki's accident.

393
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:54,946
She fell asleep at the wheel
and hit a post.

394
00:21:54,946 --> 00:21:57,349
One of the rare times
she had the kids with her.

395
00:21:57,349 --> 00:22:01,153
- Was anyone hurt?
- The kids weren't, thank God.

396
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:04,356
They were whisked away
before the police arrived.

397
00:22:04,356 --> 00:22:06,825
Ricki went to the hospital.

398
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:08,727
What happened with
Children's Services?

399
00:22:08,727 --> 00:22:11,830
Ricki had it all tidied up
before they even started looking.

400
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:13,398
Yeah, but there has
to be a police report.

401
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:15,634
There has to be hospital records.

402
00:22:15,634 --> 00:22:20,395
Power and money can make
anything go away.

403
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,480
I understand you were the attending...

404
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:30,248
the night of Ricki Austin's car accident.

405
00:22:30,248 --> 00:22:33,352
- It was nothing. Checked and released.
- Any complications?

406
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:36,021
Yeah, I had to get through
the hospital's VIP liaison...

407
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:38,490
and three of her handlers
before I could examine her.

408
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:40,659
I'm wearing a lab coat.
Who'd they think I was?

409
00:22:40,659 --> 00:22:42,461
Obviously a reporter in disguise.

410
00:22:42,461 --> 00:22:44,196
The story never made the papers.

411
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:46,231
Celebrities have to use pseudonyms...

412
00:22:46,231 --> 00:22:48,367
or the hospital would be
overrun with fans.

413
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:50,602
What name does Ricki usually use?

414
00:22:50,602 --> 00:22:52,671
Sorry, it's doctor-patient privilege.

415
00:22:52,671 --> 00:22:55,140
- So, what were the extent of her injuries?
- Off the record.

416
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,542
Minor. Head laceration
and a bloody nose.

417
00:22:57,542 --> 00:23:00,178
Way we heard it,
she was babbling incoherently.

418
00:23:00,178 --> 00:23:03,115
- She was shaken up from the accident.
- Minor as it was.

419
00:23:03,115 --> 00:23:05,650
You do a tox screen? / No.

420
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:07,886
You come in with those
exact symptoms at Bellevue...

421
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:10,522
it's automatic.

422
00:23:10,522 --> 00:23:13,592
If you'll excuse me,
I have rounds.

423
00:23:13,592 --> 00:23:16,695
Different treatment for the rich
and the poor. What's new?

424
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:20,098
Same hospital they brought Ashley.
Be nice to look at her medical history.

425
00:23:20,098 --> 00:23:22,634
It's never gonna happen
without a subpoena.

426
00:23:22,634 --> 00:23:24,469
Ashley acts out.

427
00:23:24,469 --> 00:23:28,073
I'm very fond of her,
but she's very disruptive in class.

428
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:30,575
- Class clown disruptive?
- She talks through class...

429
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:32,944
and gets upset when other students
won't talk back.

430
00:23:32,944 --> 00:23:34,346
She's starved for attention.

431
00:23:34,346 --> 00:23:36,915
Positive or negative,
it doesn't matter.

432
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:39,151
She starts fights with
the slightest provocation.

433
00:23:39,151 --> 00:23:41,486
Does Ashley have
a lot of accidents at school?

434
00:23:41,486 --> 00:23:44,756
She's fallen off bleachers,
playground equipment.

435
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:47,526
- She's always showing off.
- "Look at me" accidents.

436
00:23:47,526 --> 00:23:48,760
So what have you done about her?

437
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:52,097
When she disrupts class,
I send her to the steps.

438
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:56,601
- You make her run steps?
- No, out here.

439
00:23:56,601 --> 00:23:58,236
When a student gets in trouble...

440
00:23:58,236 --> 00:24:01,239
they're sent to step one,
for a 10 minute time-out.

441
00:24:01,239 --> 00:24:03,975
Second offense, step two.

442
00:24:03,975 --> 00:24:06,478
Ashley's a repeat step three offender.

443
00:24:06,478 --> 00:24:10,015
I think she needs help,
not punishment. / So do I.

444
00:24:10,015 --> 00:24:12,484
I sent letters home,
they were never answered.

445
00:24:12,484 --> 00:24:14,152
I finally took it to the headmaster.

446
00:24:14,152 --> 00:24:15,987
We've met him.
What did Parsons do?

447
00:24:15,987 --> 00:24:19,791
He told her parents Ashley
had to see a therapist or be expelled.

448
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:23,061
- Is therapy helping?
- She's not getting therapy.

449
00:24:23,061 --> 00:24:25,664
It didn't sit well with her parents.

450
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:29,568
But, hey, they did donate
a new library.

451
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:32,037
Where does that leave Ashley?

452
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:34,840
Out on the steps.

453
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:38,610
Anyone gets close to helping her,
Ricki buys a wall...to block them off.

454
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:41,364
And I think we've definitely hit ours.

455
00:24:41,364 --> 00:24:42,647
There's gotta be something
that we can do.

456
00:24:42,647 --> 00:24:45,584
What? They don't abuse her,
they don't criminally neglect her.

457
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:47,452
- They don't love her.
- What?

458
00:24:47,452 --> 00:24:49,921
How many unloved kids
you think there are in this city?

459
00:24:49,921 --> 00:24:53,689
It's not an SVU case anymore.
You just gotta let it go.

460
00:24:56,261 --> 00:25:01,032
Yeah, right. Hold on.

461
00:25:01,032 --> 00:25:03,679
I got the 2-7 on three.
They've got Ashley.

462
00:25:03,679 --> 00:25:04,803
Why? What happened?

463
00:25:04,803 --> 00:25:08,006
She just walked in to the desk sergeant,
then asked for you.

464
00:25:08,006 --> 00:25:11,576
- Okay, put her through.
- Remember our little talk yesterday?

465
00:25:11,576 --> 00:25:14,145
She's reaching out to me,
what am I supposed to do?

466
00:25:14,145 --> 00:25:16,539
Have a uni drive her home.

467
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:20,051
This is Benson.

468
00:25:20,051 --> 00:25:23,255
Hey, can somebody watch her?
We'll be there in about 10 minutes.

469
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:25,678
Okay.

470
00:25:26,591 --> 00:25:29,275
Don't look at me.

471
00:25:40,939 --> 00:25:42,974
- Olivia.
- Hey.

472
00:25:42,974 --> 00:25:45,710
They left you in here all
by yourself?

473
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:49,414
Officer Garvey came in for a minute,
but she had to go.

474
00:25:49,414 --> 00:25:53,318
- She wasn't that much fun anyway.
- Ashley...

475
00:25:53,318 --> 00:25:56,755
did something happen?
Are you okay?

476
00:25:56,755 --> 00:25:59,746
Yeah, I just wanted to see you.

477
00:26:01,526 --> 00:26:03,962
Didn't you have school today?

478
00:26:03,962 --> 00:26:08,166
- I ditched, then I took a cab here.
- Ashley.

479
00:26:08,166 --> 00:26:10,068
They must have called
your mother by now...

480
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:12,470
I'm sure she's worried
sick about you.

481
00:26:12,470 --> 00:26:13,738
She doesn't care.

482
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:17,542
She's probably going out of her mind.
I'm taking you home, let's go.

483
00:26:17,542 --> 00:26:21,446
- No, I wanted us to hang out today.
- We can't, I'm working.

484
00:26:21,446 --> 00:26:25,517
But I won't get in your way,
I promise. I can help you.

485
00:26:25,517 --> 00:26:27,319
Ashley, you know how
you can help me...

486
00:26:27,319 --> 00:26:29,955
you can help me by never
ever doing this again.

487
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:32,090
Do you understand that?
Now let's go, come on.

488
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:35,679
- No.
- Ashley.

489
00:26:36,795 --> 00:26:41,678
- Ashley, you're bleeding.
- I'm okay.

490
00:26:43,768 --> 00:26:47,238
Is your mother home?

491
00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:49,304
She never is.

492
00:26:55,180 --> 00:26:58,050
Come on, okay?

493
00:26:59,314 --> 00:27:02,120
HI-FREQUENCY STUDIOS
599 W. 53RD STREET
THURSDAY, JANUARY 18

494
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:07,892
