00:27:07,892 --> 00:27:15,836
¢Ü The way I love you now ¢Ü

496
00:27:16,267 --> 00:27:20,002
Ashley Austin Black,
you get in here.

497
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:27,132
Why do you do this to me?
Let me see it.

498
00:27:27,132 --> 00:27:29,347
Miss Austin, is there a place
we could speak privately?

499
00:27:29,347 --> 00:27:31,309
Detective, you really shouldn't
have gone out of your way.

500
00:27:31,309 --> 00:27:32,803
My driver would have picked her up.

501
00:27:32,803 --> 00:27:35,387
Olivia doesn't mind.
She's my friend.

502
00:27:35,387 --> 00:27:38,223
- It's important that we speak.
- This is not a good day.

503
00:27:38,223 --> 00:27:41,059
Ricki, we've only got
the studio till 4:30.

504
00:27:41,059 --> 00:27:42,927
We still have two tracks
to lay down.

505
00:27:42,927 --> 00:27:45,764
Honey, look, why don't you
just go in the green room...

506
00:27:45,764 --> 00:27:49,534
with Connie and you have her get
you something to eat, okay?

507
00:27:49,534 --> 00:27:53,004
- But can't I stay with you?
- No honey, mommy's working.

508
00:27:53,004 --> 00:27:56,474
- Then can Olivia stay with me?
- No, she can't.

509
00:27:56,474 --> 00:27:58,790
Now just go, okay?

510
00:28:01,479 --> 00:28:03,948
Thank you, Detective.

511
00:28:03,948 --> 00:28:06,799
Okay, let's try it again.

512
00:28:09,788 --> 00:28:11,823
She calls all the time.

513
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:14,025
What happens when
you have to hang up?

514
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:16,461
At first she begs to talk,
just for a few more minutes...

515
00:28:16,461 --> 00:28:19,564
and then when I have to go,
she just...

516
00:28:19,564 --> 00:28:21,132
She sounds so depressed.

517
00:28:21,132 --> 00:28:23,568
When you first met, how much
time did you spend together?

518
00:28:23,568 --> 00:28:27,839
Just a few minutes. / It sounds
like reactive attachment disorder.

519
00:28:27,839 --> 00:28:29,574
It is very common in orphans...

520
00:28:29,574 --> 00:28:32,377
who are abandoned during
their crucial bonding cycle.

521
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:36,347
They meet complete strangers
and they form instant relationships.

522
00:28:36,347 --> 00:28:38,717
So it's not just my sparkling wit?

523
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:42,220
I have one patient who meets a stranger
and she goes up and hugs them.

524
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,755
She goes to the market...

525
00:28:43,755 --> 00:28:46,558
and tells the checkout girl
that she loves her.

526
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:48,927
That fits.

527
00:28:48,927 --> 00:28:50,895
But Ashley keeps getting hurt.

528
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:54,532
It's part of the package.
And it could escalate.

529
00:28:54,532 --> 00:28:56,601
Is there treatment?

530
00:28:56,601 --> 00:28:58,970
I could start her
on corrective attachment therapy...

531
00:28:58,970 --> 00:29:01,840
but, Olivia, I'd have to see the mother
and daughter together.

532
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:04,909
It's never gonna happen.

533
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:11,416
If she's in imminent risk, Children's
Services could mandate therapy.

534
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:12,717
I'm sorry.

535
00:29:12,717 --> 00:29:15,153
Come on, there's gotta be
something that you can do?

536
00:29:15,153 --> 00:29:16,755
For emotional abuse? / No.

537
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:19,190
Ricki was reported before
for the car accident.

538
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:20,725
You did nothing about that, either.

539
00:29:20,725 --> 00:29:23,294
You're busting my shoes over this?

540
00:29:23,294 --> 00:29:26,831
I'm handling 32 families.

541
00:29:26,831 --> 00:29:30,568
I've got babies with skull fractures,
10-year-old prostitutes.

542
00:29:30,568 --> 00:29:33,304
I understand that,
I handle the same cases.

543
00:29:33,304 --> 00:29:36,227
But that shouldn't mean that this little
girl has to fall through the cracks.

544
00:29:36,227 --> 00:29:38,910
Look, it's not that I don't care.

545
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:40,812
But with a high-publicity mom
like that...

546
00:29:40,812 --> 00:29:43,882
I could spend weeks just trying
to get an appointment.

547
00:29:43,882 --> 00:29:45,250
Okay, so do it.

548
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:48,419
I've got a kid in the burn ward
about to die.

549
00:29:48,419 --> 00:29:50,054
It's triage.

550
00:29:50,054 --> 00:29:52,590
You tell me who should get
my attention the most...

551
00:29:52,590 --> 00:29:56,320
your one girl or my battered 30.

552
00:30:01,499 --> 00:30:04,068
Please ask Ricki to call me
when she gets in.

553
00:30:04,068 --> 00:30:05,540
Thank you.

554
00:30:09,774 --> 00:30:13,378
- Olivia!
- Hey, kiddo.

555
00:30:13,378 --> 00:30:15,947
- I can't believe you came.
- How you doing?

556
00:30:15,947 --> 00:30:18,449
- You have to come see my room.
- Next time, sweetheart.

557
00:30:18,449 --> 00:30:20,685
- No, please, just for a minute?
- No, I gotta go.

558
00:30:20,685 --> 00:30:22,720
Ashley, she can't come in.
Let's go. / No.

559
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,323
No, really, sweetheart.
I gotta go, next time. / No.

560
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:28,126
- Ashley, come inside.
- No, not without Olivia.

561
00:30:28,126 --> 00:30:30,128
- Make her come in.
- She can't.

562
00:30:30,128 --> 00:30:32,537
Ashley. / No.

563
00:30:32,537 --> 00:30:36,070
Ashley!
Stop! Stop! Stop!

564
00:30:40,138 --> 00:30:41,706
- Give her to me.
- Let go of me.

565
00:30:41,706 --> 00:30:44,576
- Give her to me. Get her inside.
- It's okay.

566
00:30:44,576 --> 00:30:47,312
- No!
- What's the matter?

567
00:30:47,312 --> 00:30:50,915
- What are you doing here?
- Your daughter needs help.

568
00:30:50,915 --> 00:30:54,152
- I talked to a psychologist who...
- You did what?

569
00:30:54,152 --> 00:30:56,521
This psychologist can help her.

570
00:30:56,521 --> 00:30:58,464
The thing is, she needs
to see the both of you together.

571
00:30:58,464 --> 00:31:01,159
- Leave us alone.
- Ricki, your daughter needs help.

572
00:31:01,159 --> 00:31:04,496
- Get away, before I call the police.
- Miss Austin, I am the police.

573
00:31:04,496 --> 00:31:07,910
Then it's damn lucky
I have my own security.

574
00:31:16,074 --> 00:31:17,742
Morning, Olivia.

575
00:31:20,044 --> 00:31:22,614
This doesn't look like
the makings of a pleasant day.

576
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:25,950
Ashley's called already, six times.

577
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:28,499
- What's wrong?
- Don't ask.

578
00:31:28,499 --> 00:31:32,933
- Benson, you're on desk duty.
- Captain, I can explain.

579
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:36,160
You can't follow my orders on the street,
you try keeping my files straight.

580
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:40,265
Captain... / And in case anyone else here...
has Det. Benson's hearing problem...

581
00:31:40,265 --> 00:31:42,500
read my lips or buy
the CliffsNotes.

582
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:44,936
No one is to go near
Ashley Black again.

583
00:31:44,936 --> 00:31:49,574
That includes her family, school,
house, and any employees therein.

584
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:53,207
You can't do this.
Somebody's gotta help her.

585
00:31:53,207 --> 00:31:57,641
Really. Well, thanks to you,
now none of us can.

586
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:06,357
It's a restraining order...

587
00:32:06,357 --> 00:32:09,502
against the whole unit.

588
00:32:17,468 --> 00:32:21,406
Alex, you can't imagine
how needy this little girl is.

589
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:24,976
"Needy?"  Olivia, we do
sex crimes and child abuse.

590
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:27,011
I'm sorry, but there's
not much we can do...

591
00:32:27,011 --> 00:32:28,746
for the emotionally short-changed.

592
00:32:28,746 --> 00:32:30,315
What about abandonment?

593
00:32:30,315 --> 00:32:33,051
Her parents tour nine months
out of the year.

594
00:32:33,051 --> 00:32:37,588
Her father is a documented alcoholic.
And what about Corbin?

595
00:32:37,588 --> 00:32:40,425
That was a traffic accident.

596
00:32:40,425 --> 00:32:46,130
The autopsy report lists physical
evidence of long-term stress.

597
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:49,100
He internalized, she externalizes.

598
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:52,470
- You're speculating.
- Not about Ashley's disorder.

599
00:32:52,470 --> 00:32:56,774
Ashley's tantrums,
her running away, her accidents.

600
00:32:56,774 --> 00:33:00,078
- It could only escalate.
- Olivia, why are you doing this?

601
00:33:00,078 --> 00:33:03,254
Because this kid is in trouble.

602
00:33:05,616 --> 00:33:08,052
We might have imminent risk of harm.

603
00:33:08,052 --> 00:33:10,455
There must be something
that you can do about that.

604
00:33:10,455 --> 00:33:14,819
Maybe, but we still have
one major hurdle.

605
00:33:14,819 --> 00:33:17,899
Are you trying to get fired?
Because that's the only option I have left.

606
00:33:17,899 --> 00:33:20,965
Would I put myself on the line
if I didn't know what was in store...

607
00:33:20,965 --> 00:33:23,601
- for this little girl?
- She's been hurting herself for years.

608
00:33:23,601 --> 00:33:25,370
We can subpoena her
medical records.

609
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:27,038
And her teacher and the headmaster.

610
00:33:27,038 --> 00:33:29,040
They saw the problem,
but did nothing about it.

611
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:32,977
- Parents wouldn't let them.
- What are you thinking?

612
00:33:32,977 --> 00:33:37,215
An Article 10 proceeding.
We can remove the girl from the home.

613
00:33:37,215 --> 00:33:39,250
That is gonna play great in the press.

614
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:40,852
It's family court, not criminal.

615
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:42,754
And I've already made
a couple of phone calls.

616
00:33:42,754 --> 00:33:44,689
There isn't a less disruptive avenue?

617
00:33:44,689 --> 00:33:46,324
None that Ricki can't circumvent.

618
00:33:46,324 --> 00:33:49,227
She's already circumvented us.
We're under a restraining order.

619
00:33:49,227 --> 00:33:52,791
It's an active investigation.
I'll get it lifted.

620
00:33:57,969 --> 00:34:00,748
Do it.

621
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:05,476
- Olivia!
- No, please, don't do that.

622
00:34:05,476 --> 00:34:09,856
Ashley, honey, look at me.
I want you to go with Det. Stabler.

623
00:34:09,856 --> 00:34:11,904
It's okay. I want you to go with Det.
Stabler, okay?

624
00:34:11,904 --> 00:34:13,251
- Honey, come.
- Please, no.

625
00:34:13,251 --> 00:34:15,720
- It's okay, I'll be right out.
- I don't wanna go with you.

626
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:17,688
I wanna stay with Olivia.
Let go of me!

627
00:34:17,688 --> 00:34:21,159
This isn't fair. Let go of me!

628
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:24,128
This warrant charges you
with impairment of emotional health...

629
00:34:24,128 --> 00:34:27,165
Article 10, Section 1024,
of the Family Court Act.

630
00:34:27,165 --> 00:34:28,332
Impairment of what?

631
00:34:28,332 --> 00:34:31,069
You do have the right to be
present at a hearing on Thursday...

632
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:35,244
at which time a judge will
determine Ashley's placement.

633
00:34:40,044 --> 00:34:43,314
Why are you doing this to me?

634
00:34:43,314 --> 00:34:48,698
This isn't about you,
it's about Ashley.

635
00:34:51,556 --> 00:34:54,255
I'll be back in a minute.

636
00:34:56,994 --> 00:35:00,765
- So?
- Nothing.

637
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:03,267
- Anything?
- That's it.

638
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:06,204
- I'm empty.
- No family member will take her.

639
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:09,591
No one wants to lose
their meal ticket.

640
00:35:11,576 --> 00:35:13,111
So what happens now?

641
00:35:13,111 --> 00:35:15,880
Emergency foster care
for tonight. / Where?

642
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:18,316
There's room at Laight Street.

643
00:35:18,316 --> 00:35:22,688
- I'll drop her off.
- No, I'll drive her there.

644
00:35:23,087 --> 00:35:25,490
Can we go home to
your house now?

645
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:28,626
Sweetie, we're not going
to my house.

646
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:33,297
What?
But you came and got me.

647
00:35:33,297 --> 00:35:36,434
- You don't want me to live with you?
- It's not that, Ashley...

648
00:35:36,434 --> 00:35:39,437
it's just that my house isn't
set up for kids.

649
00:35:39,437 --> 00:35:42,807
- That's okay.
- And even if it was...

650
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:44,275
I'm hardly ever there.

651
00:35:44,275 --> 00:35:48,779
You know, my work, it just...
It takes up all my time.

652
00:35:48,779 --> 00:35:52,110
You understand that,
Ashley, don't you?

653
00:36:05,229 --> 00:36:07,459
What are you still doing here?

654
00:36:08,432 --> 00:36:12,904
- You drop her off at Laight Street?
- Yeah.

655
00:36:12,904 --> 00:36:16,539
Never been there before.

656
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:22,690
It's a room filled with
a dozen cots.

657
00:36:24,248 --> 00:36:27,552
It's been about a month now,hasn't it?

658
00:36:27,552 --> 00:36:29,954
Since what?

659
00:36:29,954 --> 00:36:34,992
- Your mom.
- Where did that come from?

660
00:36:34,992 --> 00:36:38,663
Olivia, it's me.
I know the issues you had with her.

661
00:36:38,663 --> 00:36:41,799
No. No connection.

662
00:36:41,799 --> 00:36:45,002
Successful woman, rarely home,
when she was home, she was drunk.

663
00:36:45,002 --> 00:36:46,637
You were lonely and neglected...

664
00:36:46,637 --> 00:36:51,560
and you never had a chance to resolve
the thing before she died?

665
00:36:54,011 --> 00:36:57,127
You're wrong.

666
00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:04,012
I'll get you a coffee.

